			    STPJS 272</div>
  <p class="cont">with the kingdom of God? Where did the kingdom of God begin? Where there is no kingdom of God
  there is no salvation. What constitutes the kingdom of God? Where there is a prophet, a priest, or
  a righteous man unto whom God gives His oracles, there the kingdom of God; and where the oracles
  of God<span class="footRef">1</span> are not, there the kingdom of God is not.</p>
  <p class="std">In these remarks, I have no allusion to the kingdoms of the earth.<span class="footRef">2</span> We will keep the laws of the
  land;<span class="footRef">3</span> we do not speak against them; we never have, and we can hardly make mention of the state
  of Missouri, of our persecutions there,<span class="footRef">4</span> but what the cry goes forth that we are guilty of larceny,
  burglary, arson, treason, murder, &amp;c., &amp;c., which is false. We speak of the kingdom of God on the
  earth,<span class="footRef">5</span> not the kingdoms of men.<span class="footRef">6</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Need of Revelation</div>
  <p class="std">The plea of many in this day is, that we have no right to receive revelations;<span class="footRef">7</span> but if we do not
  get revelations, we do not have the oracles of God;<span class="footRef">8</span> and if they have not the oracles of God, they are
  not the people of God. But say you, What will become of the world, or the various professors of
  religion<span class="footRef">9</span> who do not believe in revelation and the oracles of God as continued to His Church in all
  ages of the world,<span class="footRef">10</span> when He has a people on earth? I tell you, in the name of Jesus Christ,<span class="footRef">11</span> they
  will be damned;<span class="footRef">12</span> and when you get into the eternal world, you will find it will be so, they cannot
  escape the damnation of hell.<span class="footRef">13</span></p>
  <div class="topic">John Held Keys of Aaronic Priesthood</div>
  <p class="std">As touching the Gospel and baptism that John preached, I would say that John came preaching
  the Gospel for the remission of sins;<span class="footRef">14</span> he had his authority from God,<span class="footRef">15</span> and the oracles of God were
  with him, and the kingdom of God for a season seemed to rest with John alone.<span class="footRef">16</span> The Lord promised
  Zacharias that he should have a son who was a descendant of Aaron,<span class="footRef">17</span> the Lord having promised that
  the priesthood should continue with Aaron and his seed throughout their generations.<span class="footRef">18</span> Let no man
  take this honor upon himself, except he be called of God, as was Aaron;<span class="footRef">19</span> and Aaron received his
  call by revelation.<span class="footRef">20</span> An angel of God also appeared unto Zacharias while in the Temple,<span class="footRef">21</span> and told
  him that he should have a son, whose name should be John,<span class="footRef">22</span> and he should be filled with the Holy</p>
